<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-617-116  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 617 116.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  July 2 1990 v7 n27 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI allots funds for net expansion, improvements. (includesrelated article on new voice features)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp plans to spend $1.2 billion in 1990 andthe same amount again in 1991 to upgrade its network.andP;  MCI'sCommon Channel Signaling System 7 network is already beingupgraded in anticipation of increased traffic volume and suchadvanced services as ISDN.andP;  Capacity will jump from 9,000 to21,000 messages per second.andP;  The Digital Data Network is alsobeing improved, and T-3 digital access and cross-connect systemswill be installed as well.andP;  The network will also be expanded.andO;The 7.5 billion calls handled in 1989 by MCI's network was anincrease of 40 percent over 1988 traffic.andP;  MCI has invested $7billion to date on its network, which is about 30 percent analogand 70 percent digital.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (communication systems).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     ExpansionNetworksPlanningT3 CommunicationsUpgradingSignaling System 7 (Computer network protocol).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>